# DIG Browser: native window.chia bridge (CHIP-0002) over a frame Mojo pipe.
#
# Re-architects the injected window.chia provider so it reaches the in-process
# DIG wallet through a frame-scoped Mojo pipe (DigWalletRpc) to the browser
# process, NOT loopback HTTP — so it is never blocked by a page's CSP, works on
# any dapp, and the browser stamps the calling frame's unspoofable committed
# origin onto each request for the wallet's per-origin approval gate.
#
# IMPORTANT: the renderer-side bridge (DigWalletBridge) is a PLAIN C++ object
# owned by ChromeRenderFrameObserver (one per frame). It installs
# window.__digWalletRpc as an ordinary v8::Object carrying a single bound C++
# function (External-backed), with NO cppgc-managed gin::Wrappable in the page
# main world — a per-page cppgc wrappable crashed the renderer on every web page
# (incident 2026-06-27). The provider JS (dig_provider.js, embedded as
# kDigProviderJs) wraps __digWalletRpc in the window.chia Promise API; its
# injection is wired in chrome_render_frame_observer.cc (windows-dig-browser-ux).
#
#   * chrome/common/dig/dig_wallet_rpc.mojom + chrome/common/BUILD.gn — the
#     frame-scoped DigWalletRpc interface (Request(json) => (json envelope)).
#   * chrome/browser/dig/dig_wallet_rpc_handler.{h,cc} — browser-side handler:
#     reads the frame's committed origin, calls the in-process wallet FFI
#     (CallWalletRpc) on a blocking thread. Bound in
#     chrome_browser_interface_binders.cc. (dig/BUILD.gn + dig_native_runtime
#     gain the handler sources + CallWalletRpc — see windows-dig-browser-ux.)
#   * chrome/renderer/dig/dig_wallet_bridge.{h,cc} + chrome/renderer/BUILD.gn —
#     the renderer bridge described above.
#   * chrome/renderer/chrome_render_frame_observer.h — owns the per-frame bridge.
#
# Generated by diffing the build tree against pristine 149.0.7827.155
# (chrome/common/BUILD.gn baseline includes windows-disable-event-log.patch,
# which precedes this patch in the series).
